1
00:00:01,230 --> 00:00:05,340
Whether you’re day trading or making long-term
investment decisions, it’s important to

2
00:00:05,340 --> 00:00:07,480
know what the markets are doing.

3
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:11,360
Often this is done with market indexes, but
these values don’t always give you the whole

4
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:13,300
picture, and oftentimes they don’t.

5
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:16,260
That’s why smart traders use market breadth
indicators.

6
00:00:16,260 --> 00:00:21,190
In today’s video, I will share the best
market internal indicators that will reveal

7
00:00:21,190 --> 00:00:23,279
to you the overall market movements.

8
00:00:23,279 --> 00:00:27,660
It may sound complicated at first if you’re
not familiar with these indicators, but trust

9
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:33,079
me, they are real game-changers and will help
you to make better decisions.

10
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:35,370
Technical analysis has one major fault.

11
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:39,649
Almost all indicators and patterns are based
on what happened in the past, not what is

12
00:00:39,649 --> 00:00:41,780
forecasted to happen in the future.

13
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:45,830
And as being a technical trader myself, I
have to always remember this when placing

14
00:00:45,830 --> 00:00:47,000
my trades.

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,210
But there are some indicators that actually
are forward looking and these forward-looking

16
00:00:51,210 --> 00:00:54,059
indicators are known as Market Internals.

17
00:00:54,059 --> 00:00:58,219
If they are used correctly, they might be
one of the best tools you can use to time

18
00:00:58,219 --> 00:01:00,879
the markets!

19
00:01:00,879 --> 00:01:05,590
Market Internals are mathematical formulas
that measure the number of advancing and declining

20
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,760
stocks, and their volume, to calculate the
participation in a stock index's price movements.

21
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:15,300
By evaluating how many stocks are increasing
or decreasing in price, and how much volume

22
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:20,000
these stocks are trading, Market Internals
help in confirming stock index price trends,

23
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,070
or can warn of future price reversals.

24
00:01:24,070 --> 00:01:27,570
Breadth indicators are primarily used for
two reasons:

25
00:01:27,570 --> 00:01:32,060
Market Sentiment: because such indicators
can help determine if a market is more likely

26
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:34,250
to rise or fall.

27
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:38,140
Trend Strength: because the indicators can
help determine the strength of a bullish or

28
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:39,610
bearish trend.

29
00:01:39,610 --> 00:01:43,380
There are many different indicators that traders
and investors can use in their analysis.

30
00:01:43,380 --> 00:01:48,290
Here are the most important ones that can
help you break down the market and what move

31
00:01:48,290 --> 00:01:51,340
it’s about to make.

32
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:56,310
First is the Advance/Decline (A/D) Line
This indicator, mostly used in the U.S. stock

33
00:01:56,310 --> 00:02:00,940
market, can be calculated on both a daily
and weekly basis and is the most basic and

34
00:02:00,940 --> 00:02:05,230
widely used indication of breadth in the major
U.S. stock exchanges.

35
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:09,470
The construction of the advance/decline line
is calculated by subtracting the number of

36
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:16,360
stocks declining on any given day, from the
number advancing relative to the prior close.

37
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:21,170
When more stocks are moving up than are moving
down, this line is advancing (it has a positive

38
00:02:21,170 --> 00:02:26,099
slope and its direction is higher) and vice
versa in a declining trend.

39
00:02:26,099 --> 00:02:30,561
These figures do not take into account stocks
that were unchanged on the day or week, but

40
00:02:30,561 --> 00:02:33,560
only those up or down from the prior close.

41
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:38,060
The value of the A/D line always begins from
some fixed starting point, and this means

42
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:40,680
that the initial value begins at 0.

43
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:45,730
What is most relevant in the advance/decline
figure is the slope of the line, not the absolute

44
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:47,090
cumulative value.

45
00:02:47,090 --> 00:02:50,329
How to Read the Advance-Decline Line
The advance-decline line is seldom used by

46
00:02:50,329 --> 00:02:51,329
itself.

47
00:02:51,329 --> 00:02:54,349
Instead, the ADL is plotted against its relevant
index.

48
00:02:54,349 --> 00:02:58,140
to confirm trends or for the likelihood of
reversals.

49
00:02:58,140 --> 00:03:01,920
There are four interpretations of the concept:
1.

50
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:06,879
Advance-Decline Line and Index Trending Upwards
A situation where the advance-decline line

51
00:03:06,879 --> 00:03:10,510
and index are both trending upwards is said
to be bullish.

52
00:03:10,510 --> 00:03:15,310
The rise in the index is driven by the rise
in the majority of stocks in the index.

53
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:20,010
As such, investors tend to believe that the
market will continue its uptrend in the near

54
00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:21,819
future.

55
00:03:21,819 --> 00:03:23,629
2.

56
00:03:23,629 --> 00:03:27,430
Advance-Decline Line Trending Downwards and
Index Trending Downwards

57
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:32,069
A situation where the advance-decline line
and index are both trending downwards is said

58
00:03:32,069 --> 00:03:33,400
to be bearish.

59
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:38,620
The decline in the index is driven by the
decline in a majority of stocks in the index.

60
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:42,730
As such, investors tend to believe that the
market will continue its downtrend in the

61
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:43,730
near future.

62
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:44,730
3.

63
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:45,730
Advance-Decline Line Trending Upwards and
Index Trending Downwards

64
00:03:45,730 --> 00:03:49,810
A situation where the advance-decline line
is trending upwards, but the index is trending

65
00:03:49,810 --> 00:03:52,889
downwards is said to be a bullish divergence.

66
00:03:52,889 --> 00:03:58,140
The decline in the index is driven by the
decline in a minority of stocks in the index.

67
00:03:58,140 --> 00:04:01,720
Therefore, it indicates that sellers are losing
their conviction.

68
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:06,870
As such, investors tend to believe that the
market will show a reversal and trend upwards

69
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:07,870
in the near future.

70
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:08,870
4.

71
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:09,870
Advance-Decline Line Trending Downwards and
Index Trending Upwards

72
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:13,659
A situation where the advance-decline line
is trending downwards, but the index is trending

73
00:04:13,659 --> 00:04:16,280
upwards is said to be a bearish divergence.

74
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:21,280
The increase in the index is driven by the
increase in a minority of stocks in the index.

75
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:25,040
Therefore, it indicates that buyers are losing
their conviction.

76
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:29,970
As such, investors tend to believe that the
market will show a reversal and trend downwards

77
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:31,170
in the near future.

78
00:04:31,170 --> 00:04:37,410
Second, we have the McClellan Oscillator
This oscillator will be applicable to equities

79
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:42,380
markets that have a substantial number of
individual stocks that trade actively.

80
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:46,870
The McClellan oscillator also provides an
indication of the trend in market breadth

81
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:51,780
and is presented in a familiar way, as a (smoothed)
difference between the number of advancing

82
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:55,030
and declining stocks on the NYSE.

83
00:04:55,030 --> 00:04:59,350
Because of the nature of momentum, a strong
bullish trend is followed by a large number

84
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:00,820
of stocks going up.

85
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:06,190
A weakening bull market is signaled by a smaller
number of stocks making large advances in

86
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:10,640
price, as discussed already with the A/D line.

87
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:16,170
Buy indications are given when the McClellan
oscillator falls into an oversold area, which

88
00:05:16,170 --> 00:05:21,110
is defined as –70 to –100, and then turns
up.

89
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:25,980
Sell signals are generated when the McClellan
oscillator rises into the overbought zone

90
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:29,960
of +70 and +100, and then turns down.

91
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:36,240
When the oscillator is above +100 or falls
below –100, it is a sign of an extremely

92
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:40,370
overbought/oversold market—such readings
can be associated with powerful bull or bear

93
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:41,800
market trends.

94
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:46,310
The rule of thumb with such extreme readings
is to assume that the existing trend has staying

95
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:50,300
power for only another couple of weeks or
somewhat longer.

96
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:56,180
Like the MACD and Stochastics models, the
McClellan oscillator is best employed looking

97
00:05:56,180 --> 00:06:00,410
for upside and downside crossovers, from within
an overbought/oversold area.

98
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:05,940
There are often crossovers, for example, in
the slow stochastic that does not occur in

99
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:08,340
either its oversold or overbought zones.

100
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:13,270
In a similar fashion, the signals that occur
in the middle ranges of the McClellan oscillator

101
00:06:13,270 --> 00:06:19,250
are best ignored without compelling other
evidence of a technical nature.

102
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:25,720
Third indicator is the Arms Index (TRIN)
The Arms Index brings in volume to its formula

103
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,900
so is a hybrid indicator, with price and volume.

104
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:34,280
The Arms Index indicates whether volume is
flowing into advancing or declining stocks.

105
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:39,030
The index shows whether more of the total
volume is advancing volume or whether more

106
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:43,750
of the total volume is declining volume, for
all stocks on that exchange.

107
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:48,590
If more volume is associated with declining
stocks on any given day, that day’s Arms

108
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:51,650
Index will wind up being above 1.

109
00:06:51,650 --> 00:06:57,090
If more volume is associated with advancing
stocks than declining stocks, the Arms Index

110
00:06:57,090 --> 00:07:01,190
will register under 1, at the close.

111
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:06,460
The Arms Index is calculated over the course
of the trading day, but the close is primarily

112
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:08,650
what is of interest.

113
00:07:08,650 --> 00:07:12,590
Extremes in the Arms Index have an inverse
relationship to the market.

114
00:07:12,590 --> 00:07:17,050
High Arms Index readings, well above 1, indicate
heavy selling pressure.

115
00:07:17,050 --> 00:07:23,470
If Arms Index closes above 1 persist over
a few or more days, this is associated with

116
00:07:23,470 --> 00:07:28,240
a likelihood that the market is oversold,
perhaps near a bottom, and might soon turn

117
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:32,770
up—in this sense the Arms Index functions
as a contrary indicator.

118
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:37,370
The idea is if everyone is selling, it might
be the time to buy.

119
00:07:37,370 --> 00:07:41,930
It depends of course on the circumstances,
but when either buying or selling activity

120
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:48,110
predominates, it gets over done, hence the
terms overbought or oversold.

121
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:51,920
Traders generally take anything under 1.0
to be a buy signal.

122
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:54,890
Conversely, a number above 1.0 is a sell signal.

123
00:07:54,890 --> 00:08:00,720
The further away you get from neutrality,
the stronger the bulls or bears are on that

124
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,720
day.

125
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:06,300
However, if TRIN gets too far away from 1.0,
it’s a sign that the market may soon reverse.

126
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:14,380
A number above 3.0 or below 0.5 could be a
sign of an imminent reversal.

127
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:19,680
Traders use market breadth indicators in conjunction
with other forms of technical analysis, such

128
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:24,400
as chart patterns and technical indicators,
to maximize the odds of success.

129
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:31,850
For example, if the Advance/Decline Line starts
to drop while the S&P 500 is still rising,

130
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:36,860
traders will watch closely for the S&P 500
to break below a rising trend line, break

131
00:08:36,860 --> 00:08:40,959
below support, or for technical indicators
to turn bearish.

132
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:45,040
This will help confirm that the price may
be starting to decline, and therefore the

133
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:48,310
trader can exit longs or initiate short positions.

134
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:54,360
If the majority of the securities tracked
by the indicator are “advancers”, then

135
00:08:54,360 --> 00:09:00,060
investors expect a rosier market going forward,
while a majority of “decliners” would

136
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:04,689
give investors pause, indicating weakening
demand for the stocks.

137
00:09:04,689 --> 00:09:10,339
Essentially, market internals point to a convergence
or a divergence in securities markets.

138
00:09:10,339 --> 00:09:15,139
If the data reveals a confirmation then the
market index being tracked will continue its

139
00:09:15,139 --> 00:09:16,139
direction.

140
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:21,360
If there’s a divergence, then the market
might steer into a different direction.

141
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:26,660
Market internals can provide a much-needed
clarity for investors, and lead to more stable

142
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:28,889
and savvy investment outcomes.

143
00:09:28,889 --> 00:09:35,569
So, by determining whether more cash is flowing
in or out of the market, breadth indicators

144
00:09:35,569 --> 00:09:40,759
can be a reliable powerful predictive tool
on market movement and momentum—one that

145
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:47,430
can give investors a big edge over the competition
on a regular basis.

146
